  </p>

  <p> Chu Li and Jose are both trying to solve the quadratic equation </p>
  <me> x^{2}+5 x=14 </me>
  <p> Jose does the following: </p>
  <md> 
    <mrow> x(x+5) = 14 </mrow>
    <mrow> x = 14, x + 5 = 14 </mrow>
    <mrow> x=14, x=9 </mrow>
  </md>

  <p> Chu Li does the following: </p>
  <md>
    <mrow> x^{2}+5 x=14 </mrow>
    <mrow> x^{2}+5 x-14=0 </mrow>
    <mrow> (x+7)(x-2)=0 </mrow>
    <mrow> x+7=0, x-2=0 </mrow>
    <mrow> x=-7, x=2 </mrow>
  </md>

  <p> Is either one correct? For incorrect solution(s) why does their proposed solution method not work? If either has a correct solution, then why does their method work: i.e. why does what they do yield actual solutions to the equation? </p>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-Solving-by-Factoring">
    <title>Solving by Factoring</title>

    <remark> <p> If <m>A*B=0</m>, then either <m>A=0</m>, or <m> B=0</m>. We call this property the <term>Zero Product Property </term>. </p> </remark>
    
    <example> 
      <p> For instance, to solve <m> 2 x^{2}+1=3 x </m> , we set the equation equal to <fillin/>, try and factor and apply the <fillin/> property. </p> 
      <p> Then we apply the <fillin/> property and solve the equation. </p>
    </example>

    <activity>
      <p> Try solving the quadratic equation <m> 3 x^{2}-7 x=6</m> using factoring. Check your answer with your neighbor. </p>
    </activity>

    <question>
