    <title></title>
    <tabular>
      <row>
          <cell> </cell> <cell bottom="minor"><m> x</m> </cell> <cell bottom="minor"> <m>-6</m></cell>
      </row>
      <row>
          <cell right="minor"><m> x </m></cell> <cell bottom="minor" right="minor"> </cell> <cell bottom="minor" right="minor"> </cell>
      </row>
      <row>
          <cell right="minor"><m> -6 </m></cell> <cell bottom="minor" right="minor"> </cell> <cell bottom="minor" right="minor"> </cell>
      </row>
    </tabular>
    </table>
    <p> What do you notice about the top right and bottom left boxes? Why does this happen? </p>
    
    <p> Try it again for a generic number <m> N: (x+N)^{2} </m> </p> 
    <table>
    <title></title>
    <tabular>
      <row>
          <cell> </cell> <cell bottom="minor"><m> x</m> </cell> <cell bottom="minor"> <m> +N </m></cell>
      </row>
