      </row>
      <row>
          <cell right="minor"><m> +N </m></cell> <cell bottom="minor" right="minor"> </cell> <cell bottom="minor" right="minor"> </cell>
      </row>
    </tabular>
    </table>

    <p> For a quadratic of the form <m> x^2+bx+c </m> we can write it in the form <m>(x+ h)^2 +</m>(stuff) the value of <m>h</m> must be <fillin/>.</p>

    <example>
      <p> Consider the equation <m>x^{2}+6 x-2=0</m>. Notice this equation does NOT factor. So, our strategy is to try and make the left hand side of the equation be of the form <m> (x+h)^{2}</m> for the appropriate choice of <m> h</m>. We start by moving the <m> 2 </m> to the other side to get the equation </p>
      <me> x^{2}+6 x=2 </me>

      <p> Let's try it again with the equation </p>
      <me> 2 x^{2}-8 x+5=0 </me>
    </example>

